Therefore, the final answer is \boxed{\text{The isometry group maintains the identity permutation, 90-degree rotation, 180-degree rotation, 270-degree rotation, reflection over the horizontal axis, reflection over the vertical axis, reflection over the main diagonal, and reflection over the other diagonal.}}<|solve|>
